      <scopecontent id="aspace_57016cd7d648609946c648fbbf90a66f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>These papers consist of correspondence and legal and financial papers of the Lathrop family of Norwich, Connecticut, and of Jonathan George Washington Trumbull (1787-1853), grandson of Governor Jonathan Trumbull of Connecticut (1710-1785) and husband of Jan Eliza Lathrop (1795-). Papers pertaining directly to the Lathrop family include letters to Daniel Lathrop (1769-1825) from his father Joshua (1723-1807) and from a nephew Joshua Lathrop (d. 1825), papers relating to the estate of the elder Joshua Lathrop, and various legal and financial papers of Daniel Lathrop and his brother Frank T. Lathrop (1798-1832). The remaining material, more than half of the collection, concerns Jonathan G. W. Trumbull and lands in the Connecticut Western Reserve of Ohio and in Michigan which he inherited through his wife from Joshua and David Lathrop. Included are correspondence with enclosed maps of lots in Ohio, deeds, receipts, bills of sale, and related items.</p>
         <p>For a chart outlining the genealogical relations of the Lathrop family, please consult the<ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://mssa.altfindingaids.library.yale.edu/mssa.ms.0725/mssa_ms_0725_genealogical_chart.pdf"
                 linktitle="Genealogical Chart"
                 show="new">Genealogical Chart</ref>. Further details are available in <title render="italic">
               <part>A Genealogical Memoir of the Lo-Lathrop Family</part>
            </title> by E. B. Huntington.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
